{
  "stem": "10181.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't really-- forgot to tell you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of the things which the Germans did at the very beginning after the invasion of Holland was-- looked very innocent.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They made everybody register, have an identity card, OK?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now this is a very innocent thing, but what-- what did they do if you were Jewish, you had to put-- they put a big J on your identity card.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And of course, the Dutch Civil Service, which continued to function, did not-- did not resign-- maybe some people resigned.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Jews, of course, were thrown out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But this Dutch Civil Service continued to function under the direction of the Germans, you know, as if nothing had happened, and they give out identity cards.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and some people realized-- well, maybe people didn't even realize at the time what it meant, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But right away you were separated because you were the only one who had a different identity card.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This is how they separated you, OK?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this was done, very easy for them, you know, because at the beginning, I guess, except for very few-- there might have been a few people who were smart who managed to maybe find a way of not getting the identity card, but I've never come across anybody but there could have been.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I imagine most people didn't.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Especially, as you went to your local registrar who knew you, so he wasn't gonna put-- if you were Jewish, he wasn't going to say no.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They just functioned under the orders of the Germans as if nothing had happened.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this is how they could identify you.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
